    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed the full 13-factor assessment for COU2 at MRL 5. The primary hemolysis claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold) presents a thorough narrative citing grid convergence studies, bench hemolysis comparisons, and Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, and the team determined that the claim is adequately supported. All seven assessed factors show achieved levels below required levels; six factors remain not-assessed. Despite these gaps, the team accepted the package on the basis of the compelling claim description and the validation results for PIV and NIH bench comparison. The structured evidentiary derivation link from the claim to supporting evidence nodes was not verified during this review cycle.",
